condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :5.01 (a) | Description :The Subsidiary Agreement has been executed on behalf of the Recipient and the IP | DueDate :15-Nov-2011
Finance Agreement :5.01 (b) | Description :The Co-execution Agreements have been executed by the respective parties | Due Date:15-Nov-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. A. 1 (a) | Description :Establish and maintain a steering committee chaired by theExecutive Secretary of the IP and comprised of representatives of each of the Co-executing agencies and SEFIN | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. A. 1 (b) | Description :Establish and maintain a technical committee which shall includerepresentatives of the respective Co-executing Agencies | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. A. 2 | Description :Maintain a Project coordination unit, with functions, staffing andresponsibilities satisfactory to the Association and set forth in the Operational Manual | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. D. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall, and shall cause the IP to, carry out the Projectin accordance with an operational manual satisfactory to the Association | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. E. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall, and shall cause the IP to, implement the EMP,the Process Framework and the IPP in accordance with their respective terms | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. A. 1 | Description :Monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepare ProjectReports in accordance with the provisions of Section 4.08 of the General Conditions and on the basis of the Project indicators |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. A. 2 | Description :The report on the execution of the Project and related plan requiredshall be furnished to the Association not later than six months prior to the Closing Date | Due Date :January 30, 2017

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. B. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall maintain or cause to be maintained a financialmanagement system in accordance with the provisions of Section 4.09 of the General Conditions | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. B. 2 | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association as partof the Project Report, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project covering the relevant semester | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. B. 3 | Description :The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited inaccordance with the provisions of Section 4.09 (b) of the General Conditions | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II. B. 4 | Description :No later than 90 days after the Effective Date, the Recipient shallhire external auditors to carry out audits based on a short list and terms of reference satisfactory to the Association | Due Date:05-Mar-2012
